div.div: Dororo, a young orphan thief, meets Hyakkimaru, a powerful ronin. Hyakkimaru's father, a greedy feudal lord, had made a pact with 12 demons, offering his yet-unborn son's body parts in exchange for great power. Thus, Hyakkimaru - who was born without arms, legs, eyes, ears, a nose or a mouth - was abandoned in a river as a baby. Rescued and raised by Dr. Honma, who equips him with artificial limbs and teaches him sword-fighting techniques, Hyakkimaru discovers that each time he slays a demon, a piece of his body is restored. Now, he roams the war-torn countryside in search of demons.
Kyoukai no Kanata: I'LL BE HERE - Mirai-hen
Action, Drama, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural
This is the second part of a two-part movie. The story takes place one year after the TV series.
Youkya na Kanojo wa Kyorikan ga Bugtteiru

Ayano Sasagawa is the unattainable flower of the class. When I rescued her from being propositioned, I suddenly found myself with her full attention...

"Thank you, Fujimura."

I was surprised to find that she even knew my name! After that, she became strangely fond of me and started hanging out with me all the time......! She brought me home on weekends and holidays, fishing for compliments as if she were a child, and even sleeping over. I was supposed to be enjoying my life as an introverted loner, but then I realized that her presence had already become a part of my daily life.......

"Are you coming over today?"
"Just you? So I'll have you all to myself!"
"......does that mean you think I'm special?"

He thought she was from another world, but now she is zero distance away.
This is a youth caste love comedy, where you are at the mercy of a girl who is too bold!

(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
Takane-san, Kimi no Koto Sukirashii yo

"I heard that Takamine-san likes you."
The head of the school discipline committee, Kengo Mashima, heard a rumor from an unknown source...... It turned out that the source was none other than Takamine-san herself, who wanted Mashima-kun to show more interest in her! But the overly serious Mashima-kun didn't get the hint: ......
"Saki Takamine, I heard you have a crush on me?"
"Why are you asking me for? ......!"
Actually, Mashima-kun liked Takamine-san, too. The first time you see these two, you'll be writhing in frustration at their innocent denseness!
(Source: Gagaga Bunko, translated)
